title: Delaware Valley's Hannah Bonaguidi rules the roost at H/W/S girls cross country
text:
Complete Box Score » 
Hunterdon/Warren/Sussex cross country championship 
Delaware Valley senior Hannah Bonaguidi took first place as an individual and North Hunterdon gained a little revenge on rival Voorhees by winning its second team title in three seasons. 
Turning point: When Bonaguidi took off from the top pack about halfway through the race, no one went with her. She powered her way alone to the finish line. 
Top performer: Bonaguidi won her first H/W/S individual crown in 18 minutes and 40 seconds. She became the first Terrier girl to win the county title. 
What it means: Bonaguidi showed she will be an individual force to be reckoned with throughout the season, as did other top finishers such as North Hunterdon’s Anna DiMarcello (second) and Voorhees' Lauren Wagner (third). The Lions won a team championship they wanted very much.
